      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 is a superlative example of the E46 chassis, maintained to a museum standard. At its heart is the S54 naturally aspirated 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS high-pressure variable valve timing system that delivers a crisp 8,000 RPM redline. Power is routed through a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission to a torque-sensing limited-slip differential. This specimen is mechanically flawless: the rear subframe has been structurally reinforced, rod bearings have been replaced as preventative maintenance, and the VANOS system has been overhauled with uprated seals. The factory M-tuned suspension, utilizing McPherson struts and a multi-link rear, remains taut with fresh bushings and original geometry. The exterior retains its factory depth and gloss, while the interior leather bolsters show no signs of compression or wear. A truly turn-key, collector-grade vehicle with a comprehensive service dossier.",
